Literary Catalogue

Complete Works.

Five published books. A biography on its way.

Novel · 2020

Bajo el cielo rosa

Published in 2020

In Epsilon, erasing memories is the only way to survive.

In the city of Epsilon, the state offers its citizens a unique service: erasing painful memories. But when the protagonist decides to undergo the process, he discovers that what is erased is not just the pain, but identity itself.

A dystopia about memory, identity, and what remains when everything is erased. One of Antonio Romeo's most daring novels.

View on Amazon

Short Stories · 2021

Modelo Standard de Acero y otros relatos

Published in 2021

What would you do if your fear of loneliness pushed you to accept a dinner with the co-worker you least stand?

A collection where the everyday twists until it embraces the most hilarious surrealism. Urban characters dragged along by inertia, conformity, and alienation: men who cling to cheap wine to survive unbearable hosts, office workers who fantasise about their own disappearance.

Cynical, direct, and brutally honest about broken relationships and the tragicomedy of trying to fit into a cold, impenetrable world that hides the unsteady heartbeat of those who desperately seek not to be so alone.

View on Amazon

Novel · 2017

Las luces de un avión

Published in 2017

«No hay nada que temer, Rafa, son las luces de un avión».

At 36, Rafa's life has been reduced to kneading pizzas, evading his past, and trying not to lose his mind in a city that isn't his. His routine escape shatters when he meets Javier, who claims his strange limp is a consequence of a UFO sighting. What begins as a delirious anecdote drags Rafa towards a mysterious extraterrestrial contact group and the enigmatic Elena.

Subjected to a dark initiation rite, Rafa's reality disintegrates completely. Trapped between amnesia, extreme paranoia, and visions of impossible lights in the sky, he must piece together a puzzle marked by a French island on the satellite, suspicions of clones, and a disappearance with no records. A suffocating journey to the limits of the mind and madness.

View on Amazon

Novel · 2024

Los mejores supermercados

Published in 2024

In the heart of Lisbon, O Patamar is an iconic bar about to disappear: Cristiano Ronaldo has acquired the building to turn it into a luxury hotel. A Spanish immigrant, whose life was transformed by a Bitcoin investment, decides to take matters into his own hands and writes a passionate letter to the President of the Portuguese Republic.

What follows is an immersion into the bar's daily life: a vegan with a fresh hair transplant, a man who claims to be Spiderman, the unbridled passion for Sporting CP. A novel where humour and irony intertwine with a critical look at modern Lisbon, sold to tourism, and the question of whether a place's charm can withstand the onslaught of unchecked progress.

View on Amazon

Novel · 2016

Montaña

Published in 2016

A village split in two. Only two inhabitants remain. And a civil servant sent from the capital.

Pedro is sent as a civil servant to Churbe, a border village split in two. Only two inhabitants remain, one on each side. What should be a bureaucratic formality becomes a journey into absurdity, into the secrets places hold, and into the nature of the limits human beings impose upon themselves.

Antonio Romeo's first novel. A fable about bureaucracy, territory, and what remains when almost everything vanishes.
